                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.111/76.]</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Some of the thirty-one Syrian firms here are unimportant retailers who could
                    easily liquidate, but others have stocks which could not be disposed of within
                    the time set, extension of which is refused by the Haitian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
